source_objects.title: Database Design & Development
source_objects.description: Become a database expert with these courses ranging from basic SQL to Hadoop and Oracle mastery.

items.title: Learn SQLite Database in Android
items.headline: Learn SQLite Database by Developing an Android App
objectives_summary: Learn about SQLite Database
How to Apply CRUD operations
How to use SQLite Database with an Android App

items.title: Data Visualization Techniques
items.headline: Gain hands-on experience in creating effective visualizations
objectives_summary: Understand, validate, and optimize your data for effective visualizations
Know how and when to use line charts, bar charts, dot plots, scatter plots, and distribution plots
Find out the best ways to maximize the impact of basic chart types

items.title: Encryption in SQL Server 2019
items.headline: A Step-by-Step Guide to Implementing Various Encryption Options in SQL Server 2019
objectives_summary: You'll learn how to define encryption technologies specific to relational databases
You'll learn the various encryption approaches in SQL Server
You'll learn how to implement many of these encryption technologies in SQL Server

items.title: The DAX Workshop - Part 2

visible_instructors.job_title: Data Engineer / Business Intelligence / Power BI / Snowflake
visible_instructors.title: Randy Minder
visible_instructors.name: Randy

items.headline: Learn DAX by working through real-world business scenarios via 30 exercises
objectives_summary: This is a hands on course, a continuation of The DAX Workshop - Part 1 . You will learn how to work through many common business related problems and scenarios.
The critical nature of the current filter context and how it affects your measures is stressed
By working through many exercises you will understand the CALCULATE function and how understanding "context transition" is essential

items.title: First Guide to Dashboards using IBM Cognos Analytics
items.headline: Combine a variety of data to gain meaningful insights, and visualize information using stunning dashboards.
objectives_summary: Build stunning dashboards with Cognos Analytics
Use the new, unified Cognos Analytics interface to create, modify, and consume reports and dashboards
Learn about the visualization capabilities available to you: how and when to use them, how to interact with them, and how to customize them

items.title: PHP Database Connections to MYSQL
items.headline: Easily to follow step by step guide to using PHP and MySQL databases
objectives_summary: use PHP to access MySQL databases
add mySQl database to your websites
create database connections with PHP

items.title: Neo4j Cypher Essential Training
items.headline: Cypher query, Neo4j, Graph Database Concepts, Query Performance, INDEX
objectives_summary: Visualize and maintain Graph Data
Solid foundation on Cypher Query Language with Hands-on exercise.
Understand Query Execution, profiling with EXPLAIN and PROFILE and performance.

items.title: Beginners MongoDB Guide along with Mongoose
items.headline: Master MongoDB Development for Web. CRUD Operations,MongooseJS - All about MongoDB!
objectives_summary: Understand how MongoDB stores data
Use all features MongoDB offers you to work with data efficiently
Gain mastery of the most popular MongoDB interface, Mongoose JS

items.title: CouchDB - Mastering Database Design with CouchDB
items.headline: Learn about CouchDB, the processes to set it up, and the ways to interact with CouchDB server using cURL and Futon.
objectives_summary: Learn how to create, update and delete databases and documents.
Understand the difference between SQL and nosql databases
Learn the mechanics of CouchDb deployment

items.title: R12i Order Management Fundamentals (on R12.2.3)
items.headline: Order Management is the core of an Oracle E-Business Suite Order-To-Cash (O2C) Solution
objectives_summary: Understand Order To Cash and Credit To Cash Process Flows
Setup and Implement Order Management, Shipping and Basic Pricing in Order To Cash Process Flow, including the dependent setups in Receivables and Inventory
Understand the Order-To-Cash Lifecycle with different order flows

items.title: Cloud Databases on AWS and AZURE
items.headline: Scalable | SQL | NoSQL | Elastic | Data Warehouse | Graph based | Document based | and more
objectives_summary: On completion of this course you would be able to develop and deploy your applications over Amazon Cloud- Amazon Web Services.
You would be in a better position to implement all DBMS concepts on AWS cloud using various kinds of database services out there.
Flexibility to develop applications with DynamoDB, Neptune, RDS, StorageGateway, etc

items.title: Introduction To SQL Server Reporting Services -SSRS
items.headline: Learn Hands-On  how to create a basic  report using SQL Server Reporting Services
objectives_summary: Configure SQL Server Reporting Services
Grant users access to the Reporting Services Server
Create a Report Server Project

items.title: Microsoft SQL Queries - Hands-on training for Business Users

visible_instructors.job_title: Microsoft Certified Instructor,  CAMS-FCI, Data Architect
visible_instructors.title: Kent Stern
visible_instructors.name: Kent

items.headline: Writing Microsoft SQL Queries - Prerequisite SQL Training for working professionals, analyst, report builders and DBA's
objectives_summary: Microsoft SQL Query Language learn to write queries that run against a Microsoft SQL Server database.
Write SQL Queries and follow along with the Instructor as you profile tables, columns and the schema.
Hands-On SQL Query language training where you will create group by and having queries

items.title: FileMaker Pro 13 for beginners
items.headline: This is a complete top to bottom course to learn database information management using FileMaker Pro for a beginner.
objectives_summary: This FileMaker Developer Course contains 12 hours of instructional lessons and 65 lectures providing top to bottom use of FileMaker Pro 13
you will learn the basics of database design and analysis
you will be able to define the database design requirements

items.title: Learning Path: Big Data Visualization
items.headline: Gain hands-on experience in creating effective visualizations of your data
objectives_summary: Find out how to utilize visualization best practices
Discover how to identify and understand your source data
Get to know how to match your dataset to the appropriate visualization type

items.title: A Beginner's Guide To Creating Database Driven Applications
items.headline: Learn how to create a database driven application with ease using oracle's APEX
objectives_summary: Create and Run Database Applications
Create and manage user accounts
Create workspace
